The introduction of   
 
  in the uncertainty principle has profound implications: 
1.
Dynamic Quantum Uncertainty
:The chance dimension introduces fluctuations in uncertainty that depend on the local spacetime 
g eometry. For example, in regions of  high spacetime curvature (e.g., near black holes),  
 
  could increase signif icantly, leading to 
observable deviations in quantum measurements. 
